Configuration file for the `ctx-cage` sandbox that runs LLM agents; copy to `.cagevars` (gitignored) to set agent-specific runtime variables distinct from `.env`, which holds only `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`.

Lines are loaded as environment variables into the caged agent's process before execution. `CTX_CAGE_EXTRA_PATH` is special: a colon-separated list of host directories to bind read-only into the cage and prepend to PATH (each entry must be an existing directory or the run fails). All other `KEY=VALUE` pairs are exported directly into the agent's environment. The cage runs under `bwrap --clearenv`, so this file is the sole source of extra variables.

Two keys are forbidden here: `CTX_CAGE_ALLOW_SPEND` (a spend-consent gate; pass `--allow-spend` to the invoking shell instead) and any key the cage already manages (`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL`, `PATH`, `HOME`, `TASK`, etc.) — attempting either causes the run to fail rather than silently override.